snippet.title: I wrote a song about Cancer/Big Pharma | "CANCER" (live acoustic version) | original song
snippet.description:
I am a female singersongwriter and I go by the name "her habits". After yet another person very close to me got diagnosed with cancer recently, I wrote this song. I've been working on a music video and a mixed/produced version of my original song "CANCER" so stay tuned as those will be coming soon.

follow me on instagram📸@herhabitschannel  https://www.instagram.com/herhabitschannel/

Spotify tracks coming eventually!
-------------------------------------------------------------

Lyrics:

"CANCER" by her habits

She said, "I have cancer" 
But I know you won't giver her the answers
My heart and common sense speak
Tell me there's deceit 
All the money you keep asking
and you come up with nothing.

CANCER, CANCER, CANCER
You know there's answers
Controlled by the gatekeepers
Censored from the masses
CANCER, CANCER, CANCER
Don't tell me you're clueless
You gloat over patents
You were never trying to cure it.

Works enough to keep us coming back
Cause if it worked too well there'd be no paycheck
Killing in the name of profit
and trust the facts, pay the tax, fill their pockets
she slips through the cracks and I go back to black

CANCER, CANCER, CANCER 
You never gave her a chance you're 
Taking my family, everything
Money, power, greed, you're living in sin
CANCER, CANCER, CANCER
Is there justice? For those who's been
Killed in the name of suppression

Cancer, Cancer, Cancer
I know your secrets
But how can I save her?
When you keep them hidden.

How can I save her?
